10. sulcis has interest because the sentence is constructionally complete at arbusta. Horace is thinking of a vineyard, on a large scale, where the vines would be planted in long rows (sulcis) with uprights joined by a support (see Shuckburgh on De Senect. 15. 52). Small holders would use no support or trellis-work.
